				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Paying Retail Employees $50,000 a Year</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-10-17T13:55:54+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">October 17, 2014 9:55 am</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">October 17, 2014 9:55 am</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/17/today-in-small-business-paying-retail-employees-50000-a-year/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Paying Retail Employees $50,000 a Year" data-description="How to create a marketing plan. Apple Pay arrives Monday. And does dressing like a man lead to success?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The United States has been <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/markets/2014/10/16/us-proves-surprisingly-resilient-despite-investor-panic-over-sputtering-global/">resilient despite</a> investor panic over a sputtering global economy.</li>
<li>Jobless aid applications <a href="//www.davisenterprise.com/local-news/associated-press/jobless-aid-applications-fall-to-14-year-low/">fall to</a> a 14-year low.</li>
<li><a href="//www.marketwatch.com/story/industrial-production-jumps-1-in-september-2014-10-16">Industrial production</a> jumped in September.</li>
<li><a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/102093376">Homebuilder confidence</a> drops.</li>
<li>The <a href="//247wallst.com/economy/2014/10/16/philly-fed-positive-on-manufacturing/?">Federal Reserve Bank of Philadelphia</a> says there is continued expansion in the regionâs manufacturing sector.</li>
<li>This round-up of <a href="//www.inc.com/gene-marks/this-round-up-of-small-business-surveys-will-make-you-feel-better.html">small-business surveys</a> will make you feel better.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s why the Container Store pays <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/the-container-store-pays-employees-50000-a-year-2014-10">retail employees</a> $50,000 a year.</li>
<li>Does dressing like a man <a href="//www.dailyworth.com/posts/3021-rethinking-gender-and-fashion-in-the-workplace?u">lead to greater</a> success?</li>
<li>Starbucks is going to <a href="//www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/10/16/starbucks-tattoos-policy-work_n_5999746.html">let its employees</a> show their tattoos.</li>
<li>Hundreds of Walmart employees <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/wal-mart-protestors-storm-park-avenue-2014-10">march outside</a> of Alice Waltonâs Manhattan apartment.</li>
<li>Walmart says it is <a href="//www.slate.com/blogs/moneybox/2014/10/16/walmart_eliminating_minimum_wage_pay_will_affect_about_6_000_workers.html">phasing out</a> minimum wage pay and <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/markets/2014/10/16/wal-mart-stores-inc-plans-ga-distribution-center-state-says-it-will-create-400/">will be creating</a> 400-plus jobs at a distribution center in Georgia.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The chief executive of Amtrak <a href="//www.citylab.com/politics/2014/10/a-chat-with-amtraks-ceo-on-the-state-of-us-passenger-rail/381538/">discusses the challenges</a> of running a national railroad.</li>
<li>The founder of GoDaddy <a href="//cnb.cx/11ulCK2">offers his views</a> on the economy.</li>
<li>Bill Gates has <a href="//www.aei-ideas.org/2014/10/bill-gates-has-a-big-idea-for-tax-reform-and-its-excellent/?">a big idea</a> for tax reform.</li>
<li>Marcus Lemonis talks about <a href="//www.inc.com/david-whitford/marcus-lemonis-on-growing-comnpanies-and-shrinking-cupcakes.html?cid=sf01001">why Crumbs cupcakes</a> are now smaller.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s a guide to <a href="//blogs.salesforce.com/company/2014/09/small-business-marketing-strategy.html">creating a marketing plan</a>.</li>
<li>And here&#8217;s how <a href="//juntaedelane.com/how-to-repurpose-content-to-maximize-your-marketing-dollar/?">to re-purpose</a> content to maximize your marketing dollar.</li>
<li>Hooters is <a href="//www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/10/16/the-misogynistic-companies-jumping-on-the-breast-cancer-bandwagon.html">asking</a> people to âGive a Hootâ about breast cancer.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Wendyâs has <a href="//adage.com/article/digital/wendy-s-beef-latest-creative-consultant-facebook/295357/?u">had success online</a> mostly due to its digital partner, Facebook.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Ebola</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A New York businessman claims heâs &#8220;<a href="//www.tmz.com/2014/10/15/ebola-c-supplement-ny-businessman-todd-spinelli-wafer/">making a killing</a>&#8221; off Ebola.</li>
<li>Ebolaâs <a href="//finance.yahoo.com/news/panic-profiteer-or-capitalist--selling-ebola-domain-name-for--150k-182117698.html?s">domain name</a> is for sale for $150,000.</li>
<li>African journalists are <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3037218/fast-feed/african-journalists-developing-digital-tools-to-fight-ebola">harnessing technology</a> to fight rumors and misinformation around the struggle to contain the deadly disease.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s why <a href="//www.marketplace.org/topics/health-care/why-travel-ban-so-tough-pull">a travel ban is tough</a> to pull off.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Up</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Six things to do when <a href="//www.huffingtonpost.com/lauren-jessen/6-things-to-do-when-start_b_5997426.html?">starting a business</a> with a sibling.</li>
<li>A start-up <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/238612">wants to streamline</a> the process of painting a room.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A major settlement means Detroit <a href="//www.rawstory.com/rs/2014/10/major-settlement-puts-detroit-closer-to-pulling-itself-out-of-bankruptcy/">may soon be pulling</a> itself out of bankruptcy.</li>
<li>Regulators in Washington State are <a href="//www.northwestgeorgianews.com/associated_press/news/national/washington-puts-pot-sales-fines-online-for-banks/article_d0fd2480-5551-11e4-b2fd-0017a43b2370.html">trying to make it easier</a> for financial institutions to track customers in the marijuana industry.</li>
<li>A new competitor to Uber in New York will raise <a href="//www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20141015/TECHNOLOGY/141019918/a-new-uber-antagonist-rises-in-nycs-car-wars">driver pay</a>.</li>
<li>Thereâs a <a href="//money.cnn.com/interactive/pf/north-dakota-baby-boom/index.html">baby boom</a> in North Dakota.</li>
<li>Detroit&#8217;s mayor <a href="//www.wxyz.com/news/duggan-personally-apologizes-to-business-owners-that-were-ticketed-by-mistake-for-graffiti-art">apologizes</a> to business owners who were ticketed by mistake for graffiti art.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>An Australian restaurant is <a href="//www.springwise.com/australia-restaurant-soup-waste/">making soup</a> out of waste.</li>
<li>Office Depot plans to <a href="//news.yahoo.com/office-depot-cut-1-100-jobs-europe-134557702--finance.html">cut 1,100</a> jobs in Europe.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Washington</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The JOBS Act <a href="//www.inc.com/jeremy-quittner/equity-crowdfunding-platforms-soldier-on-without-title-three.html">was supposed</a> to allow smaller investors to buy shares of private companies through crowdfunding.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A day after HBOâs announcement, CBS says it too will <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/cbs-launches-online-subscription-video-service-1413465013?">offer an online subscription service</a>.</li>
<li>Google&#8217;s <a href="//www.pcworld.com/article/2835082/googles-ambitious-broadband-plans-include-testing-wireless-technology-filing-shows.html#tk.rss_all">ambitious broadband plans</a> include testing wireless technology.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Opportunities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>After last <a href="//abcnews.go.com/Business/wireStory/snow-ice-profit-small-businesses-26217782">year&#8217;s rough winter</a> and with forecasts for another snowy season, some small-business owners are planning to make money.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A Texas plant will <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/17/business/energy-environment/texas-plant-to-capture-and-then-reuse-carbon.html">capture and reuse carbon</a>.</li>
<li>This is everything <a href="//thenextweb.com/apple/2014/10/16/everything-apple-announced-ipad-mac-event/?">Apple announced</a> at an event yesterday (and Dr. Ruth <a href="//mashable.com/2014/10/16/dr-ruth-apple-ipad-event-tweets/?">tweets</a> a sexy recap).</li>
<li>Apple Pay <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/238618">officially arrives</a> Monday, and the financial services industry is &#8220;<a href="//www.bloomberg.com/video/marc-andreessen-on-apple-pay-bitcoin-and-apple-tv-RQXUYGJyTqOTO8Lvg76WEA.html">freaking out,</a>&#8221; according to Marc Andreesen.</li>
</ul>
